<DOC><DOCNO> AP880513-0285 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-13-88 1624EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u f PM-WallStreetClosing     05-13 0142</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0152</SECOND><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The stock market chalked up a broad gain today,inspired by falling interest rates and a steady dollar in foreignexchange.   As the dollar strengthened against leading foreign currencies,prices of long-term government bonds rose as much as $5 for each$1,000 in face value in the credit markets.   Analysts said investors around the world were encouraged by thesuccessful completion late Thursday of the Treasury's three-dayauction of $26 billion in bonds and notes.   Brokers also noted that there were no unpleasant surprises inthe Labor Department's report this morning that the producer priceindex of finished goods rose 0.4 percent last month.   In addition, Japan reported a continued narrowing of itsinternational trade surplus. The Commerce Department is due toreport next week on the latest monthly U.S. trade balance.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>